{
  "saved_at": 1775212573.3545098,
  "signature": "678597f53d0cf4d7674772b7720183811657a2e9",
  "source_url_hash": "d0dae201af31d66bda7a4e56f9a0a014498cd37c",
  "metadata": {
    "video_id": "03op5ZA9OYs",
    "title": "",
    "duration": 0,
    "thumbnail": ""
  },
  "source_transcript_segments": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 8.4,
      "text": "Most people start learning to code by picking a programming language, Python, JavaScript, C++, yeah?"
    },
    {
      "start": 8.4,
      "end": 14.24,
      "text": "You need it to write code, but what really makes someone a high-level programmer isn't how well they know syntax."
    },
    {
      "start": 14.24,
      "end": 18.8,
      "text": "It's how well they solve problems. And that's a skill most tutorials never teach."
    },
    {
      "start": 18.8,
      "end": 21.92,
      "text": "Let me show you what I mean. A while back."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.92,
      "end": 26.88,
      "text": "I was building a small app that needed to show the top three most used words in a text file."
    },
    {
      "start": 26.88,
      "end": 29.44,
      "text": "Sounds easy, right? At first, I'd"
    },
    {
      "start": 27.98,
      "end": 34.14,
      "text": "At first, I jumped straight into code, opened VS Code, imported libraries started typing"
    },
    {
      "start": 34.14,
      "end": 35.14,
      "text": "loops."
    },
    {
      "start": 35.14,
      "end": 37.78,
      "text": "10 minutes later, I was completely stuck."
    },
    {
      "start": 37.78,
      "end": 39.44,
      "text": "My logic was messy."
    },
    {
      "start": 39.44,
      "end": 43.94,
      "text": "My output was wrong, and I remember thinking I know Python."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.94,
      "end": 46.02,
      "text": "So why can't I solve this?"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.02,
      "end": 47.02,
      "text": "Then it hit me."
    },
    {
      "start": 47.02,
      "end": 48.58,
      "text": "I was coding too soon."
    },
    {
      "start": 48.58,
      "end": 50.22,
      "text": "I wasn't solving the problem."
    },
    {
      "start": 50.22,
      "end": 52.26,
      "text": "I was just writing syntax."
    },
    {
      "start": 51.61,
      "end": 55.73,
      "text": "I close my editor and wrote the problem in plain English."
    },
    {
      "start": 52.26,
      "end": 53.06,
      "text": "I closed my."
    },
    {
      "start": 55.73,
      "end": 58.17,
      "text": "Find the most common words in a text."
    },
    {
      "start": 58.17,
      "end": 61.89,
      "text": "Then I asked, how would I do this if I had to do it by hand?"
    },
    {
      "start": 61.89,
      "end": 63.89,
      "text": "First I'd list out all the words."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.89,
      "end": 66.77,
      "text": "Then count how many times each one shows up."
    },
    {
      "start": 66.77,
      "end": 68.69,
      "text": "Finally then sort them by frequency."
    },
    {
      "start": 68.69,
      "end": 69.69,
      "text": "Boom."
    },
    {
      "start": 69.69,
      "end": 71.29,
      "text": "That's the actual logic."
    },
    {
      "start": 71.29,
      "end": 72.77,
      "text": "No code needed yet."
    },
    {
      "start": 72.77,
      "end": 76.49,
      "text": "Once I had that clear in my head, the code almost wrote itself."
    },
    {
      "start": 76.49,
      "end": 79.33,
      "text": "Before I typed anything, I wrote the steps, 1."
    },
    {
      "start": 79.33,
      "end": 80.33,
      "text": "Read the file."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.16,
      "end": 86.4,
      "text": "Two, split the words, three, count them, four, sort and print the top three, then I coded"
    },
    {
      "start": 80.33,
      "end": 81.33,
      "text": "2."
    },
    {
      "start": 81.33,
      "end": 82.33,
      "text": "Split the words."
    },
    {
      "start": 86.4,
      "end": 89.04,
      "text": "each step one by one."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.04,
      "end": 90.24,
      "text": "Testing as I went."
    },
    {
      "start": 90.24,
      "end": 94.0,
      "text": "It felt slow, but I wasn't guessing anymore, I was building."
    },
    {
      "start": 94.0,
      "end": 98.6,
      "text": "That's when I realized high-level programmers don't start with how do I write this."
    },
    {
      "start": 98.6,
      "end": 101.2,
      "text": "They start with how do I think about this."
    },
    {
      "start": 101.2,
      "end": 105.76,
      "text": "When my result was off by one word, I didn't just fix it, I traced why."
    },
    {
      "start": 105.76,
      "end": 108.0,
      "text": "I found out punctuation was breaking my words."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.49,
      "end": 111.17,
      "text": "My punctuation was breaking my word splits, so I cleaned the text before counting."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.17,
      "end": 116.45,
      "text": "That one small fix taught me more about thinking clearly than any syntax tutorial ever did."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.45,
      "end": 120.17,
      "text": "Because every bug tells you how your brain assumed wrong."
    },
    {
      "start": 120.17,
      "end": 121.61,
      "text": "So yeah?"
    },
    {
      "start": 121.61,
      "end": 125.41,
      "text": "Learning a language is great, but writing code is the easy part."
    },
    {
      "start": 125.41,
      "end": 126.41,
      "text": "Thinking clearly?"
    },
    {
      "start": 126.41,
      "end": 128.21,
      "text": "That's the real skill."
    },
    {
      "start": 128.21,
      "end": 132.41,
      "text": "Every time you slow down, break things down, and trace your thinking, you're training"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.32,
      "end": 135.48,
      "text": "After thinking, you're training your brain to solve problems like a real developer."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.41,
      "end": 132.85,
      "text": "your brain."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.48,
      "end": 141.12,
      "text": "If you want to learn the fastest way to level up as a developer in 100s, watch my next video."
    },
    {
      "start": 141.12,
      "end": 144.44,
      "text": "It'll show you how to turn any coding challenge into something you can actually do."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.884,
      "end": 144.884,
      "text": "challenge into something you can actually handle."
    }
  ],
